                    <msContents>
                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT7248PrMaftehe"/>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> መፍትሔ፡ ሥራይ፡ ፍታሕ፡ ሥራየ፡ ዓይነ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወብእሲት፡ አድኅን፡ ይቤለከ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ 
                                ክርስቶስ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <gap reason="illegible"/></incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT7258FetahQ"/>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ፍታሕ፡ ቅሕዱዳን፡ ቅሕዱዳን፡ ቅሕዱዳን፡ አርክያን፡ እምንስቲት፡ መኪርያ፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT7252FetahSeray"/>
                            <note>Contrary to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><citedRange unit="page">132</citedRange>
                                </bibl>, who saw in this text four different prayers for the undoing of charms.</note>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.1">
                                <title type="complete" ref="LIT7252FetahSeray#Aganent">Prayer for undoing the charms of devils and Bāryā, the charms of priests and of deacons</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ፍታሕ፡ ሥራየ፡ አጋንንት፡ ወባርያ፡ ሥራየ፡ ካህናት፡ ኪን፡ ወካህናት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡
                                    </incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.2">
                                <title type="complete" ref="LIT7252FetahSeray#Tor">Prayer for undoing the ties of death, the charms of Dask and Bāryā, the charms of Mǝč and of ʿaynat, the charms of magicians
                                    and priests</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በእንተ፡ ጦር፡ በዝንቱ፡ አስማት፡ ግበር፡ ዘፈታሕከ፡ ማእሰሪሁ፡ ለሞት፡ ሥራየ፡ ደስክ፡ ወባርያ፡
                                    ሥራየ፡ ምቼ፡ ወዓይነት፡ ሥራየ፡ ኪን፡ ወካህናት፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.3">
                                <title type="complete" ref="LIT7252FetahSeray#Rakon">Prayer for undoing charms</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ራኮን፡ ፍታሕ፡ ፈታሕኩ፡ ቀርነለው፡ </incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.4">
                                <title type="complete" ref="LIT7252FetahSeray#Sefanzer">Prayer for undoing charms</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ስፋንዝር፡ ፯ፍታሕ፡ ወዘርዝር፡ ሰዓር፡ ወመንዝር፡ አስማተ፡ ሥራይ፡</incipit>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT4604Salot"/>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ቍርጸት፡ ዌጼቤ፡ ዌጼቤ፡ ዌጼቤ፡ ዌፌኑ፡ ዌፌኑ፡ ዌፌኑ፡ ዌፌኑ፡ ዌፌኑ፡</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
